8. Expected Contributions

· Empirical: First randomized trial of a structured AI facilitation protocol that isolates the protocol effect via rotating facilitators, fixed‑effect modeling, and explicit measurement of dissent preservation, human agency, and facilitator fidelity.
· Methodological: Formal definitions and measurement strategies (DPS, retention score, semantic clustering threshold, rubric‑based proposal quality, structured facilitator log) for AI‑mediated collective intelligence; replicable facilitator protocol.
· Practical: Open‑source toolkit and facilitator guide for community use.

